The 30-Nov-00, Jason Faramus wrote:

> If anyone at all is interested or can offer me their sevices then let me
> know, I already have a very detailed plan of how it would work so it just
> needs to be put into motion. I really need some good coders to work on the
> different sections of the program (which is why I joined this list. I'm
> very impressed! ;) So please, like I said let me know what you all think.

One thing you should take into account is that most Amigans today, at least
the ones I talk to and so forth doesn't like to have the OS being taken
over, in this case the so called 'Blitz-mode'. I do belive that this is a
general idea amung the Amigans today, with exceptions.

It also depends on what machine you're aiming for, most amigans today are
blessed with at least some Fastram and a commonly used 030 (especially the
A1200).  And remember, AGA can be VERY slow when you start using it, but if
you know the hardware tricks and are aiming for higher specs Amigas, then
you might wanna give standard AGA a go.

;--
If you're going for Blitz Basic in conjunction with OS-friendly programming,
what I can suggest is using Mildred which is a chunky-mode system for
Blitz, a quite easyhandled thing too.
It does support both AGA and RTG screenmodes and holds the normal
Blitz-gfxroutines + a lot of nice other features and will get you started
in a second.

Just check it out and ask if you need any help with it.

//Thor
