All this talk of fps reminds me of Quake coding discussions. The fps rate depends on two things:-

How long the computer takes to do the instructions you tell it to between frames - also whether (and this is sometimes essential unless you want a very high fram rate) you synchronise it with the refresh rate of the screen. I think that's something like Wait Vbl - however I also user AMOS so check it out first wby pressig help on the keyword to get the syntax for the Wait command.

