Hi Jason

> of then please do. But really I would like a silky smooth frame rate, is this
> still possible with Mildred and chunky graphics modes?

I think 040/25 (but they suck anyway, 030/50's are effectively faster :) 
gets you 25fps on AGA. If you were to use Mildred with a graphics card, 
you'd probably get 50fps, as you won't need to do the chunky to planar 
conversion.

> * A 256 colour (debatable) Blitz mode display/ single playfield
>     maybe with extra background layers if speed permits. 

You'd struggle with the extra background layers I think, since you'd 
probably need to have the most background layer as a bitmap and then blit 
the layers in front of that.

>     Would this give us a good frame update as we are not blitting anything
>     yet.

Correct about all the sprite stuff. Yes, it would still run at full speed.

> Does all this sound feasible? And would I be able to pull of the same sort of
> thing with Mildred? Also does Mildred support transparency? Maybe some neat

Yes, sounds feasible apart from the background layers thing. For an example 
of most of this stuff with Mildred, have a look on the Mildred Support Site 
at http://www.stationone.demon.co.uk. There's an example of a Defender game 
(or is it Revenge of the mutatnt camels?) which does layers of parallax 
scrolling for the ground and clouds I believe, and obviously blits for the 
main ship/enemies/etc.

I don't think Mildred supports transparency, although with a 256 colour 
palette, you'd probably just be easier not doing real transparency, but 
having a section of palette for the shades. Or maybe even do the same as 
crap fighter, and have the shadows cross hatched.


