@NODE "Mail_54" " Re: File Notification "
From: John Mason <ah210@chebucto.ns.ca>
Date: 11-24-00 00:40:56
Subject: @{b}Re: File Notification@{ub}

On Fri, 24 Nov 2000, Nick Clover wrote:

> Does anyone know how to use file notification with blitz?

Yep. :)  

Here's a general overview of how I did it, let me know if you need more
details.

First you need a message port set up.  Once you have that, do something
like this:
    
   deftype .NotifyRequest nreq

   nreq\nr_Name = fname.s              ; file to watch
   nreq\nr_Flags = #NRF_SEND_MESSAGE   ; notify us with a message
   nreq\nr_Stuff\nr_Msg\nr_Port = *msgport ; use address of your msgport
   
   if StartNotify_(&nreq)<>0
     addresult = True   ; success!
     endnotify_(&nreq)
   Else
   ; failed!
   EndIf

This will set up the notify, (don't do the endnotify() until you want to
stop) once you've done that, you'll get a message on the message port when
the file changes.  I basically wait until GetMsg_ on the port returns
nonzero.


Hope this helps!

@ENDNODE

