The new local vet, Nick Knight, got into old Daisy up to their elbow.
Inside they found My Blitz Problem.

> But I dont realy know what I am doing.  Can anyone help me .  

Is that the entire code for your game? I hope not :)

But if it is, you might want to see if you can get any cheap/free books on
game techniques. Looking like you are just wanting to use Blitz mode,
you'd be safe enough getting an AMOS book on general game techniques
(although I think most might explain that as an introduction) as the
techniques will be the same, although the code will not. I say AMOS books
here, because I think there was only ever 1 written for Blitz :(

A couple of links you might want to have a look at instead of getting a
book are:

http://freespace.virgin.net/jason.hayman/BlitzCBL   (very good)
http://www.csc.liv.ac.uk/~fish/HTML/blitzman        (good, but not complete)

However, the basic steps you need to do are this:
    1) Load/create graphics, sound etc
    2) Create 2 (or more) bitmaps for display
    3) Create display
    4) Start of main loop.
    5) Display bitmap on screen and use a bitmap not being displayed
    6) Get input from user (joystick/keyboard/mouse)
    7) Update player positions
    8) Update non-player positions (e.g. the enemies)
    9) Check for collisions between player/bullets/enemies/scenery/etc
   10) Do whatever depending on the result of step 9 (e.g. remove enemy
       from screen, kill player, etc)
   11) Draw player/bullets/enemies to bitmap not being displayed
   12) Wait for display syncrhonisation
   13) Repeat main loop until end of game conditions have been met (e.g.
       player dies, all enemies killed, whatever)

I'd still recommend you go and look at BlitzCBL (from the link above).
Actually, ignore the thing about an AMOS book and my rantings and just go
straight to the BlitzCBL page. It will take your through each step and
give you code as you do it.

