I don't make any claims on how well this works or how fast it is. It
shouldn't use too much memory though. Basically you calculate a random
start position and then work back until you find a newline character. Then
you read a line to give you a random line (hopefully :).


If ReadFile(0, "dictionary.txt")
    FileInput 0
    startpos.l = Rnd(Lof(0))
    while a$<>chr$(10) AND startpos>=0
        startpos = startpos - 1
        FileSeek startpos
        a$=Inkey$(1)
    wend
    a$=Edit$(256)
    PopInput
    CloseFile 0
End If

NPrint a$ ; should be a random line of text from the dictionary file

